revenue in its own right, with the possibility of winning a greater share if
it retains its audience.
At the same time, James Capel is downgrading its growth estimates for UK
commercial television this year from 8 per cent to 6 per cent without
including inflation.
As a result, James Capel is reducing its profit forecasts for most of the
ITV companies and argues that most ITV share prices should now 'at least
pause for breath'.
