<HEADLINE>
FT  30 APR 92 / World News in Brief: Black offered Daily News
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Canadian publisher Conrad Black, owner of The Daily Telegraph, has been
given a month to buy the New York Daily News, the Daily News said. It has
been seeking a buyer since the publishing empire of its last owner, the late
Robert Maxwell, collapsed.
