The New Zealand parent will buy sufficient shares to maintain the current
level of its shareholding in FCC, leaving 4.8m shares for the public.
FCC has a debt load of CDollars 626m, equal to about 40 per cent of total
capital. The company said it was keen to reduce its debt-equity ratio, but
had no expansion plans.
