Union Discount has agreed to sell part of its 'big ticket' leasing business
to Humberclyde Investments for Pounds 20.2m.
Union, which recently reported heavy losses, is one of London's nine
discount houses through which the Bank of England channels liquidity to the
commercial banking system and influences interest rates. It said the sale
represented 44.6 per cent of its total 'big ticket' leasing book.
</TEXT>
