FT  28 APR 92 / Levitt case sent to crown court
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
   THE PROSECUTION of Mr Roger Levitt
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
chairman of the collapsed Levitt group - and three other men was yesterday
transferred from Bow Street Magistrates Court for trial at Southwark Crown
Court.
Mr Levitt is charged with 62 offences involving Pounds 20m. The charges
include conspiracy to defraud, theft, false accounting, obtaining property
