<HEADLINE>
FT  28 APR 92 / Virgin launches 'Mid Class' travel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
VIRGIN ATLANTIC Airways is to follow other intercontinental carriers by
offering three classes of travel.
The company launched its 'Mid Class' service yesterday for passengers who
have paid full price for economy tickets. They will have a separate cabin
and more legroom.
Until now, Virgin has sold seats only in economy class and upper class,
where prices were roughly comparable with business class on other airlines.
Fewer than 4 per cent of Virgin passengers pay the full transatlantic
economy one-way fare of between Pounds 334 and Pounds 404. Discounted
tickets can be as cheap as Pounds 99 but there are restrictions on travel
dates.
Virgin hopes Mid Class will push the proportion of full-fare passengers up
to 10 per cent.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 8
</PAGE>
</DOC>
