FT  28 APR 92 / London investors guide launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LONDON'S chamber of commerce is this week launching what it claims is the
first recent comprehensive guide aimed at potential foreign investors in the
capital.
The guide is a directory and promotional effort, necessitated, according to
the chamber, by the absence of a capital-wide local authority.
It surveys property, financial and labour markets and offers advice on
locations, services, transport and local government.
Ms Jacqui Ginnane, the chamber's chief economist, said: 'There has been a
steady decline in investment in London since the late 1980s and it is vital
that someone puts the case for London.'
</TEXT>
